New Records: The Cubs almost set a season high with eight runs scored in an inning, which they achieved earlier on Aug. 26 against the Pirates.
Key Match Events: The Cubs scored seven runs in the top of the second inning, which was a key turning point in the game.
Cody Bellinger hit a two-run homer during the seven-run inning.
The Nationals scored three runs in the bottom of the ninth inning, including a potential game-winning rally led by Dylan Crews.
Post-Match Reflections: Cody Bellinger expressed pride in the team's ability to respond after being down early in the game.
Keegan Thompson was praised for his clutch performance in relief, securing the save with a key strikeout.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cubs have won 10 of their last 13 games and are five games back from the final NL Wild Card spot.
The Cubs' offense has been particularly strong, scoring 80 runs in their past eight games.
